-- Germany's DAX Index Advances for Third Day; Adidas, Volkswagen Lead Climb
-- B y   A n d r e w   R u m m e r
-- 2010-10-07T12:58:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/dax-benchmark-fluctuates-basf-declines-shares-of-infineon-demag-gain.html
German stocks rose for a third day as
Adidas AG and Volkswagen AG advanced. The DAX Index climbed 0.7
percent to 6,312.25 at 2:57 p.m. in Frankfurt, having earlier
lost as much as 0.6 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
